<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Daemon_(mythology)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=11" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://people.vanderbilt.edu/~james.p.burns/chroma/practices/demontill.html" class="external text" title="http://people.vanderbilt.edu/~james.p.burns/chroma/practices/demontill.html" rel="nofollow">Maureen A. Tilley, "Exorcism in North Africa: Localizing the (Un)holy"</a> explores the meanings of <i>daimon</i> among Christians in Roman <a href="/wiki/Africa_(province)" title="Africa (province)" class="mw-redirect">Africa</a> and exorcism practices that passed seamlessly into Christian ritual.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.ccel.org/fathers2/ANF-05/anf05-116.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.ccel.org/fathers2/ANF-05/anf05-116.htm" rel="nofollow">Ante-Nicene Fathers, vol V:</a> Cyprian, "On the Vanity of Idols" e-text Daemons inhabiting the images of gods</li>
